-- S. Korea Companies to Spend 2 Trillion Won to Reduce Emissions
-- B y   S h i n h y e   K a n g
-- 2012-05-24T02:30:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-24/s-korea-companies-to-spend-2-trillion-won-to-reduce-emissions.html
South Korean companies including
Samsung Electronics Co. and Posco will spend 2 trillion won
($1.7 billion) this year to build energy-efficient facilities
and upgrade manufacturing processes to reduce carbon dioxide
emissions. The South Korean government will provide financial
measure to encourage companies to cut emissions, the Ministry of
Knowledge Economy said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shinhye Kang at 
 skang24@bloomberg.net  